{"timestamp":1771853623827,"location":"generation","stage":"PHASE10_SCORE_FULL","data":{"lessonId":"203-SYM1A","total":93,"grade":"Strong","breakdown":{"beginnerClarity":27,"teachingBeforeTesting":25,"markingRobustness":16,"alignmentToLO":15,"questionQuality":10},"issueCount":3,"issues":[{"id":"1","category":"Beginner Clarity","jsonPointers":["title","topic","description"],"excerpt":"203.SYM1A — Electrical Symbols (Noob): Why the Shapes + How to Read Them","problem":"The lesson title, topic, and description focus on 'Electrical Symbols', but the content is entirely about the electrical supply chain and distribution network (LO5).","whyItMatters":"A beginner selecting a lesson on symbols will be confused by a lesson on power stations and pylons, leading to a cognitive mismatch between expectations and content.","alignmentGap":"GENERAL PEDAGOGY"},{"id":"2","category":"Marking Robustness","jsonPointers":["blocks[4].content.questions[0].expectedAnswer"],"excerpt":"[\"gas nuclear wind and solar power\", \"gas nuclear wind and solar\", \"gas nuclear wind solar\"]","problem":"The expected answers for a list of four items in a short-text field are highly rigid and do not account for variations in order (e.g., 'Wind, solar, gas, and nuclear').","whyItMatters":"Students who know the correct generation methods but list them in a different sequence will be incorrectly marked as wrong, causing frustration.","alignmentGap":"AC1"},{"id":"3","category":"Marking Robustness","jsonPointers":["blocks[7].content.questions[0].expectedAnswer","blocks[7].content.questions[4].expectedAnswer"],"excerpt":"[\"400000\"]","problem":"The numeric expected answers are strictly limited to the base number without allowing for common technical notation (e.g., '400kV' or '400,000' with a comma).","whyItMatters":"In a vocational context, '400kV' is the more common professional shorthand; failing to accept it or variations with commas creates unnecessary friction.","alignmentGap":"AC2"}]},"sessionId":"generation"}
