{"timestamp":1772490736765,"location":"generation","stage":"PHASE10_SCORE_FULL","data":{"lessonId":"203-4L1E","total":87,"grade":"Strong","breakdown":{"beginnerClarity":26,"teachingBeforeTesting":22,"markingRobustness":20,"alignmentToLO":10,"questionQuality":9},"issueCount":4,"issues":[{"id":"I1","category":"alignmentToLO","jsonPointers":["/blocks/3/content/content"],"excerpt":"Protective earthing is a core requirement for Automatic Disconnection of Supply (ADS).","problem":"AC2 (Identify ADS component parts) is not sufficiently addressed. While earthing is mentioned as a requirement, the other specific 'component parts' of an ADS system (such as overcurrent protective devices or main earthing terminals) are not explicitly identified as part of the ADS framework.","whyItMatters":"Students need to recognize ADS as a system of parts working together; failing to list the components prevents them from meeting the assessment criteria for AC2.","alignmentGap":"AC2"},{"id":"2","category":"teachingBeforeTesting","jsonPointers":["/blocks/9/content/questions/0","/blocks/9/content/questions/4"],"excerpt":"If a fault occurs on a 230V circuit with an earth path resistance of 0.25 ohms, what is the resulting fault current?","problem":"The lesson includes Ohm's Law calculations (P1 and P5) despite the metadata explicitly stating 'noCalculations' and 'identificationOnly'. Furthermore, the mathematical formula/method was not formally taught in an explanation block.","whyItMatters":"Testing a skill (calculation) that was explicitly excluded in the scope and not formally taught creates a 'cold' question that frustrates beginners.","alignmentGap":"GENERAL PEDAGOGY"},{"id":"3","category":"beginnerClarity","jsonPointers":["/blocks/1/content/terms"],"excerpt":"vocab block","problem":"The term 'ADS' (Automatic Disconnection of Supply) is used in the text but is missing from the vocabulary definitions and is never explicitly defined in plain language.","whyItMatters":"ADS is a technical acronym central to the AC; without a clear definition, the 'Automatic' and 'Disconnection' functions remain abstract concepts.","alignmentGap":"AC2"},{"id":"4","category":"beginnerClarity","jsonPointers":["/blocks/3/content/content","/blocks/4/content/questions/1"],"excerpt":"All exposed metal parts... expectedAnswer: ['exposed conductive parts']","problem":"Terminology drift. The explanation uses the plain-language 'exposed metal parts', but the practice question's expected answer uses the technical syllabus term 'exposed conductive parts' without having introduced it.","whyItMatters":"Inconsistent terminology between teaching and testing can lead to marking failures or learner confusion when they encounter the technical term in exams.","alignmentGap":"GENERAL PEDAGOGY"}]},"sessionId":"generation"}
